there’s so much tradition and history tied to the millrose games but this year, we’re bringing a bit more youth and diversity to the mixed zone as the magic boost will have more than a dozen rising content creators covering the event. 

we’re coming up on two years of providing opportunities and mentorship for them across video, podcasting, social media, photography, writing, and graphic design. this squad is enriching and diversifying how the athlete stories are told. 

many thanks to @raypflynn & @armorynyc for welcoming these fresh voices and perspectives! it took months to plan this week with @pdxpixbykp, @satellitesisterliz, @bucksan, @jgabriel16, @codinpdx + @sharonamckee and i’m pumped to see the storytelling that comes out of this group over the next few days.

the race is underway! honored to be part of the @releaserecoveryfoundation team competing in @thespeedproject – a 340-mile race with no set course or spectators.

we’re certainly not going to win but we are trying to make the biggest impact by fundraising for scholarships that go toward people struggling with addiction or substance use and can not afford treatment otherwise. 

@releaserecovery and @zwclark have introduced me to people who have gotten a second chance at life because they got help. the hope is that someone else gets that chance with the funds that we raise while on this journey.

thanks to everyone who has donated so far. if you want to consider making a contribution, the fundraising page is linked in my bio. 

let’s do this. 🏴 

🏃‍♂️ me, @gregtravers_, @schwartzybear, @jordymadd, @karagracedudley + @molbakes 

🚌 @doug.levy, @jasonada, @emilyybanaszynski, @i_luch 

📷 @jzsnapz | 🎥 @grace__steel

THE SPEED PROJECT • A JOURNEY FROM LA TO VEGAS ON FOOT

Our @releaserecoveryfoundation team is cruising through Death Valley and we’ve already raised more than $36,000 for scholarships going toward those who can’t afford to get help for addiction recovery.

This is hard but we’re getting closer to Vegas every step.

Thank you to everyone who has donated so far. If you’re interested in making a contribution, you can find the fundraising page through the link in my bio.

🎥 @jzsnapz

WE DID IT! 

As a team, the @releaserecoveryfoundation ran 340 miles from Los Angeles to Las Vegas in 45 hours and 26 minutes. 🏃‍♂️ 

More than $41,000 raised toward the funding scholarships for those struggling with addiction and can’t afford treatment on their own. Thanks to everyone who donated! The fundraising page is still going strong! 🙏 

Thanks to my teammates @schwartzybear, @molbakes, @gregtravers_, @jordymadd and @karagracedudley for making this truly memorable. 

We couldn’t have done it without our amazing support crew that comprised of @doug.levy, @i_luch, @jasonada, @emilyybanaszynsk, @grace__steel + @jzsnapz 🚌 

Of course, thanks to @karilynncotone encouraging me along the way to push through the pain and do it for those who can’t. 🫶 

More to come upon further reflection but first some much-needed rest and celebration! 🎊

call me kate bush because i am running up that hill 😤

I'm still recovering from the most special day of my life so far. 

Those close to me know that I meticulously planned and rehearsed the surprise proposal to @karilynncotone over the last few months in great detail. Yes, there was even a PDF with maps, secret group chats and several scouting trips I made to the West Village. But even with all the preparation, nothing could have prepared me for the overwhelming flood of emotions that came with that one magical moment.

What made it even more special was being surrounded by our dearest friends and family right after. We cannot begin to express how grateful we are for each and every person who showed up to celebrate with us. We always talked about the day when all our friends from high school, college, running and theater would come together in one joyous moment – and it finally happened. Having my family and her sister and mom pop out at the end was the perfect surprise.

The love and support we received from our people (near and far) was beyond measure and I am still overcome with gratitude for everyone who helped make this day so unforgettable. 

Thank you from the bottom of our hearts. ♥️ 

📸 @pacephoto + @jzsnapz

Evidence I can keep up with a 2:19 marathoner…💨 

I guess 8 miles at a nice 7:02/mile pace with @keiradamato is considered “conversational pace” as we had a fun morning in Central Park before she raced the @nyrr Mini 10K. 

@jzsnapz biked alongside us to film a wide-ranging interview on the run that touched on all things including her training, the “world’s fastest mom” title, U.S. Olympic Marathon Trials, our @survivorcbs plans and much more. 

🎥 The full video is up on the @citiusmag YouTube channel now. For the best viewing experience, pull it up while you’re in a treadmill and it will feel like you’re jogging with some pals.

This is like Michael Jordan inviting you for a pickup basketball game on his home court.

My own training this year has been up and down with travel and work but I could not pass up on the opportunity to join @kipchogeeliud and the @nnrunningteam for a 10K easy run. The “easy” part is up for debate when you’re at 8,000+ feet of altitude and jet lagged. 

Maybe flew a little bit too close to the sun by trailing the greatest marathoner of all-time and eventually got dropped but it was totally worth it.

More to come from my first-ever trip to Kenya, including videos and one-on-one podcast episodes with Eliud + @faithkipyegon + @geoffreykamworor + @abdinageeye. Stay tuned on @citiusmag. 🇰🇪 

📸 @vincentriemersma
